JOS – Plateau State Governor Simon Lalong has congratulated Minister of Transportation Rotimi Amaechi, Minister of Transport on the conferment of the chieftaincy title of “Dan Amana” on him by the Daura Emirate Council in Katsina State. Governor Lalong in a message of felicitation made available to Saturday Independent, described the conferment of the title of “Dan Amana,” (the trusted one) on the Transport Minister as another testimony and recognition of his achievements over the years and his vision of building bridges between various parts of the country. According to Lalong, the decision of the Daura Emirate Council to honour Rt. Hon. Amaechi is a welcome development that clearly shows that Nigerians love one another and are committed to building a united, peaceful and prosperous society that engender harmonious relationships between people of different cultures. I Did Not Turban Ameachi For Monetary Gains –  Emir Of… 2023: Youths Unveil Rescue Nigeria Mission For Yahaya Bello In… He charged the Minister to continue to work hard in collaborating with other well-meaning Nigerians in the journey towards strengthening the nation’s democracy and pushing for the development of critical infrastructure such as the railways, where he has exhibited uncommon patriotism and passion to deliver on the President’s mandate of reviving the nation’s rail system. Governor Lalong also congratulated the Emir of Daura His Royal Highness Alhaji Faruk Umar Faruk for considering the Transport Minister for the honour through the title, saying the gesture is a plus to nation-building. Lalong also congratulated businessman and philanthropist, Alhaji Nasiru Danu who was also turbaned as Tafida Babba of Daura.